      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Donald J. Eberly is the Honorary President of the International Association for National Youth Service 
and the founding director (1966) of the National Service Secretariat in the USA.  He is the author of 
<emph render="italic">National Service: A Promise to Keep</emph> (1989), 
<emph render="italic">National youth service: What do we know</emph> (1985), 
<emph render="italic">Service Without Guns</emph> (2006), and other books and articles on pacifism and 
national service.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Donald J. Eberly Papers</emph> consists of printed material, reports, by-laws, and 
other material, primarily relating to Eberly's work with the National Service Secretariat.  There is also a presentation 
from the Eleanor Roosevelt Centennial Conference in October, 1984.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
